\section{Stories of individual actions}
\label{sec:stories_individual_actions}
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

Edgar McGregor picked up litter in a popular Los Angeles county park at least one
hour per day for 589 consecutive days~\cite{npr030821}. 
He earned more than \$400 from recyclable materials he collected and, on at least 
one day, he filled a dumpster with a thousand pounds of trash. 
While laudable and environmentally friendly, were his actions \emph{necessary} for
\emph{sustanability}?
To put it another way, would the park have continued to function as a park if 
Edgar McGregor had not removed the litter?



