There are many things that individuals can do to make their lives more sustainable 
in transport.

\paragraph{Individual+Choices+Transportation}
Individuals can decide which vehicles to buy or rent.
Choosing a \emph{used} vehicle
will prevent additional carbon being embodied in the vehicle itself.
Choosing a \emph{smaller} car will reduce carbon emissions 
associated with commuting.
Individuals should not ``over buy'' cars.
(If a truck is needed once per year to pull a trailer, rent.)
Choosing an electric vehicle will reduce CO$_2$ emissions
in those places where grid electricity contains a large proportion of renewables.
(See Section~\ref{sec:electric_vehicles} and Figure~\ref{fig:tesla}.)
Donâ€™t fly.
